# =============================================================================
# COMMENTS AND DOCUMENTATION
# =============================================================================

# This .gitignore file is designed for Terraform projects with the following goals:
# 1. Protect sensitive information (state files, variables, credentials)
# 2. Exclude generated and temporary files
# 3. Maintain clean repository with only source code
# 4. Support multiple development environments and tools
# 5. Follow Terraform and general development best practices

# Key principles:
# - Never commit terraform.tfvars (may contain secrets)
# - Never commit .tfstate files (contain sensitive resource information)
# - Never commit .terraform/ directory (contains cached providers and modules)
# - Always commit .tfvars.example files (provide templates for others)
# - Always commit .terraform-version files (ensure version consistency)

# For team collaboration:
# - Share terraform.tfvars.example with example values
# - Document required variables in README.md
# - Use environment variables for sensitive values when possible
# - Implement proper secret management for production environments
